  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel your <strong>butternut squash </strong>and cut in half using a sharp knife,</p><p>Tip: Drizzle the knife with a little vegetable oil for easier chopping</p><p>Scoop out the seeds with a spoon and discard, then slice, lengthways, into wedges</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1668518416991-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1668518416991-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1668518416991-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1668518416991-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1668518416991-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>butternut squash wedges</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined<strong> </strong>baking tray with your <strong>ground cumin</strong>,<strong> ground turmeric</strong>, a generous drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the butternut squash is cooked through and tender – these are your <strong>spiced butternut squash wedges</strong></p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1668518422046-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1668518422046-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1668518422046-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1668518422046-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1668518422046-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>pine nut & seed mix</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden, then transfer to a small bowl and set aside</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1668518425276-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1668518425276-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1668518425276-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1668518425276-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1668518425276-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Crush your <strong>cardamom pods </strong>open by squashing them with the side of a knife</p><p>Return the pan to a medium-high heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>crushed cardamom pods</strong>, <strong>dried lime leaves</strong>, <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>garam masala </strong>and <strong>curry powder </strong>and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until slightly thickened</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1668518429000-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1668518429000-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1668518429000-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1668518429000-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1668518429000-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[125ml]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>[150ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once slightly thickened, add the <strong>vegetable stock </strong>and <strong>creamy single soy </strong>to the pan and bring to the boil</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 15-20 min or until the sauce has thickened to a curry-like consistency – this is your <strong>makhani sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1668518432592-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1668518432592-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1668518432592-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1668518432592-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1668518432592-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the sauce is thickening, chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>with the <strong>toasted pine nut & seeds</strong> – this is your <strong>seed crumble</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1668518437514-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1668518437514-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1668518437514-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1668518437514-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1668518437514-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>roti</strong> to a separate baking tray and sprinkle them with a little <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 3-4 min or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1668518441169-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1668518441169-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1668518441169-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1668518441169-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1668518441169-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spiced butternut squash wedges </strong>over the <strong>makhani sauce</strong> and <strong>warmed roti </strong>to the side</p><p>Sprinkle over the<strong> seed crumble</strong></p><p>Tip: Watch out for any cardamom pods and lime leaves!</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
